<item>
            <title>[PAY-3509] 2.1 Legacy Payments API &#8212; Enrich Payment.Debit.Submitted with Status Fields</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3509</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a compliance officer,&lt;br/&gt;
I want the Legacy Payments API to publish enriched Payment.Debit.Submitted events with decline status and transaction limit details when a transaction exceeds the merchant&apos;s configured limit,&lt;br/&gt;
So that the Compliance Monitor can detect and alert on limit breaches from legacy payment processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This story enriches the existing PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent in the Legacy Payments API with status fields and adds a new publish call at the transaction limit breach rejection point. The existing success-path publish is also updated to include status: &quot;Approved&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AcceptanceCriteria&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Acceptance Criteria&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Business Criteria (Non-Technical):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; a merchant&apos;s transaction exceeds their configured high transaction amount limit in the Legacy Payments API&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the transaction is rejected&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; a payment event is published with decline status, rejection reason, attempted amount, and configured limit&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; the rejection response is not delayed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; a merchant&apos;s transaction is approved in the Legacy Payments API&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the event is published on the success path&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; the event includes status: &quot;Approved&quot; (backward-compatible enrichment)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-1: Decision Tree Validation (First Task &#8212; Gate)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; the Legacy Payments API codebase&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the developer investigates Event Grid infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; one of:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(a) IEventPublisher exists, Event Grid configured, PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent already published &#8594; proceed with AC-2 through AC-6&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(b) Event Grid NOT wired up &#8594; STOP and escalate to architect (scope expansion)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(c) Unclear &#8594; search for IEventPublisher, EventGridEventPublisher, PublishAsync, PaymentDebitSubmitted and document findings before proceeding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-2: Event Model Enrichment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; the existing PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent class in Legacy Payments API&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; modified&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; six new properties added: Status (string, non-nullable), StatusMessage (string?), RejectionReason (string?), RejectionCode (string?), ConfiguredTransactionLimit (decimal?), MerchantName (string?)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;JsonPropertyName&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; attributes match the architecture payload contract&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-3: Decline-Path Event Publishing&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; a transaction that exceeds the merchant&apos;s configured limit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the limit check fires (INSIDE the check block, BEFORE throwing the rejection)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; Payment.Debit.Submitted is published with all enrichment fields populated for declined status&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; publishing uses await with try/catch (fire-and-forget pattern)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; publish failure does NOT prevent the rejection response&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-4: Success-Path Event Enrichment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; the existing success-path publish of Payment.Debit.Submitted&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; a transaction is approved&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; the event includes status: &quot;Approved&quot;, rejection fields are null&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; existing subscribers see no behavioral change (additive fields only)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-5: Contract Test Alignment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; the contract test fixture payment-debit-submitted-declined-event.json from Story 1.1&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the Legacy API&apos;s PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent is serialized with declined status&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; the JSON structure matches the fixture schema for all enrichment fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC-6: Fire-and-Forget Safety&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Given&lt;/b&gt; the decline-path publish call&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt; the publish throws any exception&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Then&lt;/b&gt; the exception is caught and logged at Warning level&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; the transaction rejection response proceeds unaffected&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And&lt;/b&gt; the pattern uses await with try/catch (NOT _ = PublishAsync() or Task.Run())&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;TechnicalRequirements&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Technical Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;FIRST TASK (gate): Execute Legacy API Decision Tree per architecture. If Event Grid is not wired up, STOP and escalate.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Modify existing PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent.cs &#8212; add 6 new properties with &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;JsonPropertyName&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; attributes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Locate the transaction limit check in the payment handler/controller&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add decline-path publish call INSIDE the limit check block, BEFORE the throw/rejection&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Modify existing success-path publish to include Status = &quot;Approved&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add unit tests for all scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;RequirementsFulfilled&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Requirements Fulfilled&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FR1, FR2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Relations&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Relations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Blocked by: Story 1.1 (
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro resolved&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;PAY-3507&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3507&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;1.1 Event Subscription Wiring, Consumer Event Model &amp;amp; Contract Test Fixture&quot; &gt;
