                                                            <comment id="85857" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 09:45:16 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Follow-up (2026-06-11): rail-aware compliance-alert labeling &#8212; closes open Finding #1.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This story shipped the 4 enrichment fields but omitted &lt;tt&gt;rail&lt;/tt&gt;, which was logged at the time as open &lt;em&gt;Finding #1&lt;/em&gt; in the Dev Agent Record. That gap materialized in production: Legacy &lt;b&gt;card&lt;/b&gt; (CNP/CP) per-transaction limit declines were published with the same &lt;tt&gt;declineReason == &quot;PerTransactionLimitExceeded&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; as ACH and routed through the single canonical &lt;tt&gt;PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; (ADR-006) &#8212; but with no rail discriminator, so every card breach was emailed using the &lt;b&gt;ACH-branded&lt;/b&gt; subject and body.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The architecture already specified the fix: &lt;tt&gt;rail&lt;/tt&gt; is a canonical event field and ADR-006 says the email reflects the rail. So this is closing a doc-vs-code drift, not new scope.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What changed:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Publisher (payments-api):&lt;/em&gt; added &lt;tt&gt;Rail&lt;/tt&gt; to the Legacy &lt;tt&gt;PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/tt&gt; + &lt;tt&gt;PaymentRail&lt;/tt&gt; constants; &lt;tt&gt;ForPerTransactionLimitExceededDecline&lt;/tt&gt; now stamps the rail at all three card decline sites (&lt;tt&gt;ProcessCard&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; CNP, &lt;tt&gt;ChargeCard&lt;/tt&gt; v2 &#8594; CNP, &lt;tt&gt;ChargeCardPresent&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; CP).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Consumer (compliance-monitor-ms):&lt;/em&gt; &lt;tt&gt;PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; maps rail &#8594; payment-method label; &lt;tt&gt;EmailContentService&lt;/tt&gt; renders {{&lt;tt&gt;paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt;}} in subject + body.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Template (wellfit-resources):&lt;/em&gt; the per-transaction limit email switched from hard-coded &quot;ACH&quot; to the {{&lt;tt&gt;paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt;}} token.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Deliberate deviation:&lt;/em&gt; rather than the raw rail value (&lt;tt&gt;CP&lt;/tt&gt;/&lt;tt&gt;CNP&lt;/tt&gt;/&lt;tt&gt;ACH&lt;/tt&gt;), the alert uses friendlier wording &#8212; &lt;b&gt;CNP/CP &#8594; &quot;Card&quot;&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;ACH &#8594; &quot;ACH&quot;&lt;/b&gt; (unknown/absent &#8594; &quot;ACH&quot; for backward-compat).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tests:&lt;/em&gt; payments-api 14/14, compliance-monitor 46/46 (incl. rail&#8594;label and subject/body rendering).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;PRs (GHE):&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Code &#8212; Wellfit/wellfit-payments#263&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Template &#8212; Wellfit/wellfit-resources#58&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Story doc &#8212; Wellfit/bmad-wellfit#2901&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt; the Legacy Payments API has migrated &lt;b&gt;ADO &#8594; GHE&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;wellfit-payments&lt;/tt&gt; (&lt;tt&gt;src/services/payments-api&lt;/tt&gt;); this work landed there. The blob-template body wording takes effect per-environment once &lt;tt&gt;wellfit-resources&lt;/tt&gt; is deployed (the subject is rail-correct from the code PR alone).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                                                            <comment id="86190" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2026 07:18:44 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Moved to WAITING REVIEW.&lt;/em&gt; Summary of the change set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Problem&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Problem&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Card (CNP/CP) per-transaction limit declines were published with the same &lt;tt&gt;PerTransactionLimitExceeded&lt;/tt&gt; reason as ACH and routed through the ACH-branded compliance alert &#8212; so a &lt;em&gt;card&lt;/em&gt; breach was emailed as an &lt;em&gt;&quot;ACH&quot;&lt;/em&gt; alert. The decline reason is rail-agnostic, but the legacy &lt;tt&gt;PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/tt&gt; carried no rail discriminator and the compliance consumer + template were ACH-specific.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Changes&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Changes&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Publisher &#8212; payments-api&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Added &lt;tt&gt;Rail&lt;/tt&gt; (&lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;JsonPropertyName(&amp;quot;rail&amp;quot;)&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;) to the legacy &lt;tt&gt;PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/tt&gt;; added &lt;tt&gt;PaymentRail&lt;/tt&gt; constants.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ForPerTransactionLimitExceededDecline&lt;/tt&gt; now requires &lt;tt&gt;rail&lt;/tt&gt;, stamped at the three card decline sites: &lt;tt&gt;ProcessCard&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; CNP, &lt;tt&gt;ChargeCard&lt;/tt&gt; v2 &#8594; CNP, &lt;tt&gt;ChargeCardPresent&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; CP. V2 already stamps &lt;tt&gt;Rail = &quot;ACH&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;, so the ACH side needed no change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Consumer &#8212; compliance-monitor-ms&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;PerTransactionLimitExceededProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; maps &lt;tt&gt;Rail&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; payment method (CNP/CP &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;Card&lt;/tt&gt;; ACH/unknown/absent &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;ACH&lt;/tt&gt;, backward-compatible for pre-rail events).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;EmailContentService&lt;/tt&gt; renders the {{&lt;tt&gt;paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt;}} token in the subject and body.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A non-null rail outside the known vocabulary (CNP/CP/ACH) still defaults to ACH but now emits a Debug &lt;tt&gt;UnrecognizedRail&lt;/tt&gt; log, so future rail drift (ADR-006 anticipates Wallet/Apple Pay) or a publisher typo is visible rather than silent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Companion &#8212; wellfit-resources&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Template made rail-neutral. Title: &lt;tt&gt;ACH Per-Transaction Limit Exceeded&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; {{&lt;tt&gt;paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt; Per-Transaction Limit Exceeded}}. Body: &lt;tt&gt;An ACH payment was declined&#8230;&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;This {{paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt; payment was declined&#8230;}}.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Loggingconvention%28additionalscope%2Cisolatedcommits%29&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Logging convention (additional scope, isolated commits)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Applied the compliance-monitor logging convention (mirrors 
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;PAY-3627&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-3627&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;Derive Worldpay MaxTransactionAmount = MAX(card, ACH); event-driven resync (fix PAY-3610)&quot; &gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;icon&quot; src=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium&quot; /&gt;
            PAY-3627
        &lt;/a&gt;
                                                    &lt;span class=&quot;aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-current jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf&quot;&gt;In Stage&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
): new convention doc, dropped full-object &lt;tt&gt;@paymentEvent&lt;/tt&gt; / &lt;tt&gt;@databaseEvent&lt;/tt&gt; PII dumps in favour of shape-only logging, recipient kept to the &lt;tt&gt;EmailService&lt;/tt&gt; boundary only, and &lt;tt&gt;Stopwatch&lt;/tt&gt; entry/exit pairs added. Rail fix and logging work are in separate commits (&lt;tt&gt;eda9542c&lt;/tt&gt; + &lt;tt&gt;32e1ee03&lt;/tt&gt; = rail only).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Tests&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Tests&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;payments-api unit: &lt;b&gt;14 passing&lt;/b&gt; (factory + serialization incl. &lt;tt&gt;rail&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;compliance-monitor: &lt;b&gt;174 passing, 0 failing&lt;/b&gt; &#8212; includes new coverage that an unrecognized non-null rail still labels ACH, the &lt;tt&gt;UnrecognizedRail&lt;/tt&gt; Debug log fires on drift, and known/absent rails do not trip it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Deployordering%28actionforrelease%29&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Deploy ordering (action for release)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;wellfit-resources&lt;/tt&gt; template replacement is dictionary-driven: a token with no entry stays &lt;em&gt;literal&lt;/em&gt;. The template must &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; reach an environment before the code deploys there, or live emails render the raw {{&lt;tt&gt;paymentMethod&lt;/tt&gt;}} token. Deploy resources &lt;em&gt;with or after&lt;/em&gt; &lt;tt&gt;compliance-monitor-ms&lt;/tt&gt; per environment; the reverse (code first) is safe &#8212; the token degrades to a no-op.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;PRs&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;PRs&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Code: &lt;tt&gt;Wellfit/wellfit-payments#263&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Template: &lt;tt&gt;Wellfit/wellfit-resources#58&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
